---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { t, localizedPath } from "../i18n/utils";

const lang = "en" as const;
---

<BaseLayout title={t(lang, "about.title")} description={t(lang, "about.subtitle")} lang={lang}>
  <div class="fade-in">
    <h1 class="font-display text-3xl font-extrabold text-ink sm:text-4xl">{t(lang, "about.title")}</h1>
    <p class="mb-10 mt-3 text-lg text-neutral-400">{t(lang, "about.subtitle")}</p>
  </div>

  <div class="prose prose-invert prose-lg max-w-none fade-in">
    <p>
      Jorsby is a <strong>mass video-production studio</strong>. We produce episodic content
      at scale — vertical dramas, short-form channels and long-form documentaries — that
      businesses run on their <strong>own channels</strong> to win the one thing a banner ad
      can't: attention people choose to give.
    </p>

    <p>
      Drama is the oldest growth hack there is. People will watch fifteen episodes of a
      story they care about and scroll past a fifteen-second ad without a thought. So we
      don't make ads. We make <strong>series</strong> — characters, tension, cliffhangers,
      a reason to come back tomorrow — for Instagram, TikTok and YouTube, in any language.
    </p>

    <h2>What we make</h2>

    <p>
      Whatever your audience will actually watch — and we already run the full range on our
      own channels: a werewolf romance drama, a daily science-and-curiosity channel,
      first-person biographies of history's great minds, dark chapters of Ottoman history,
      the anatomy of billion-dollar business collapses, and short moral tales that make a
      scrolling thumb stop. Across six shows and dozens of episodes, in Turkish and English,
      the through-line is story and a consistent world people recognize episode after episode.
      See them all on the <a href={localizedPath("/work", lang)}>work page</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>How we work</h2>

    <p>
      We write, produce, voice and edit entire series with AI. That collapses what used to
      take a crew, a cast and a calendar into a pipeline that turns a brief into
      ready-to-post episodes in days — and lets us ship the same story in every language
      you publish in, with localized voices instead of subtitles.
    </p>

    <h2>The flagship series</h2>

    <p>
      <em>Married to the Alpha Who Ruined Me</em> is our flagship — a supernatural romance
      produced end to end in English and Turkish with a consistent cast across every
      episode. It's the show that proved the pipeline; the rest of the slate followed. Watch
      it on the <a href={localizedPath(`/shows/married-to-the-alpha`, lang)}>show page</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Who's behind it</h2>

    <p>
      <strong>Serhat</strong> — founder. Builds the production pipeline, directs the
      stories and obsesses over the first three seconds of every episode.
    </p>

    <h2>Work with us</h2>

    <p>
      If you want a series your audience will actually follow, <a href={localizedPath("/contact", lang)}
        >tell us what you want to make</a
      > — we'll come back with a concept and a quote before you commit to anything.
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
